#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2019-12-18-why-graalvm-19-2.adoc:8
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"layout: post\n"
"title: 'Delay in GraalVM 19.3 support - planned for Quarkus 1.2 - here is "
"why'\n"
"date: 2019-12-18\n"
"tags: announcement graalvm\n"
"synopsis: For Quarkus 1.1.0.Final, we had to take the hard decision to go "
"back to GraalVM 19.2 while our CR1 used 19.3. Here is why.\n"
"author: ebernard\n"
"---\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2019-12-18-why-graalvm-19-2.adoc:11
msgid ""
"One of the highly anticipated features of Quarkus 1.1.0.CR1 was the GraalVM "
"19.3 support.  GraalVM 19.3 changes quite a lot of things (JDK 11 preview "
"etc) and due to the deep integration between Quarkus and GraalVM, it was an "
"all-or-nothing update for us as we couldn't support both GraalVM 19.2 and "
"19.3 at the same time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2019-12-18-why-graalvm-19-2.adoc:15
msgid ""
"While porting Quarkus to GraalVM 19.3, we hit several regressions, some due "
"to Quarkus not doing the right thing (we fixed them), some due to GraalVM "
"regressions (we are working hand in hand with the GraalVM team to fix "
"them).  The next micro bugfix release of GraalVM is planned for mid-January, "
"so any workaround had to come from Quarkus and by writing substitutions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2019-12-18-why-graalvm-19-2.adoc:17
msgid ""
"Even if it wasn't pretty, the end result was solid enough that we decided to "
"ship CR1 with GraalVM 19.3 support."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2019-12-18-why-graalvm-19-2.adoc:21
msgid ""
"And, yet, our 1.1.0.Final is back to GraalVM 19.2.  It was a hard decision, "
"believe us, especially with all the work invested to get things ready for "
"1.1.  So why this step back?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: upstream/_posts/2019-12-18-why-graalvm-19-2.adoc:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "We don't want to break our promise"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2019-12-18-why-graalvm-19-2.adoc:26
msgid ""
"One of Quarkus promises is that the ecosystem works equally well on any JVM "
"and as GraalVM native image executables.  And you can build native images "
"with no hassle on your side."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2019-12-18-why-graalvm-19-2.adoc:28
msgid "A number of issues were deviating from this line:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2019-12-18-why-graalvm-19-2.adoc:30
msgid ""
"https://github.com/oracle/graal/issues/1927[a concurrency issue striking "
"randomly] made the native image build fail sometimes"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2019-12-18-why-graalvm-19-2.adoc:31
msgid ""
"The Neo4J extension and more generally the Neo4J driver support no longer "
"works in GraalVM 19.3: https://github.com/oracle/graal/issues/1995"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2019-12-18-why-graalvm-19-2.adoc:33
msgid ""
"a couple of Apache Camel Quarkus integration tests were no longer able to "
"work in native image mode either due to "
"https://github.com/oracle/graal/issues/1971.  While we could have lived with "
"the latter, it also means it could happen to any of your applications."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2019-12-18-why-graalvm-19-2.adoc:36
msgid ""
"With these regression, we were already on the fence and already had taken "
"some remediation (see below).  But we found another one that is core to "
"Quarkus promise."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: upstream/_posts/2019-12-18-why-graalvm-19-2.adoc:37
#, no-wrap
msgid "RSS (memory) usage regression"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2019-12-18-why-graalvm-19-2.adoc:41
msgid ""
"After the 1.1.0.CR1 release, we got reports that our RSS usage numbers at "
"startup were not as good as before.  RSS measures the resident size of the "
"process i.e. all the memory consumed by the process."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2019-12-18-why-graalvm-19-2.adoc:45
msgid ""
"Our measures show Quarkus 1.1 with GraalVM 19.2 at 14MB after first "
"request/response is served.  And GraalVM 19.3 bumped it to 63MB.  Because "
"memory consumption for Quarkus is a core value, we decided to hit the revert "
"button and take more time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2019-12-18-why-graalvm-19-2.adoc:49
msgid ""
"Investigations are happening between the Quarkus and the GraalVM team to "
"remediate this.  If you are interested in knowing more about it, see "
"https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/issues/6136[the Quarkus issue] and "
"https://github.com/oracle/graal/issues/1984[its companion GraalVM issue].  "
"As soon as we get to the bottom of this one, the path to Quarkus on GraalVM "
"19.3 will be cleared."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: upstream/_posts/2019-12-18-why-graalvm-19-2.adoc:50
#, no-wrap
msgid "So now what?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2019-12-18-why-graalvm-19-2.adoc:53
msgid ""
"Well, first, be prepared to downgrade your GraalVM installation to 19.2.1 "
"for the upcoming 1.1.0.Final."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2019-12-18-why-graalvm-19-2.adoc:57
msgid ""
"We are full steam to bring GraalVM 19.3 support in our next release (and "
"hopefully GraalVM JDK 11 support too).  The concurrency issue is already "
"fixed in GraalVM master, that lets us with the low-level issues.  Our goal "
"is to help the GraalVM team understand and fix these issues and get all of "
"this backported to GraalVM 19.3.1."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2019-12-18-why-graalvm-19-2.adoc:62
msgid ""
"But more fundamentally, we do not want that to happen again: discovering "
"these late in the game is not fun.  To be able to catch these issues "
"earlier, we are setting up a set of CI jobs that will check that the whole "
"Quarkus ecosystem (core extensions + quickstarts + Camel extensions + other "
"external extensions) plays well with GraalVM master.  This is a bit "
"challenging as it's (GraalVM) master on (Quarkus) master on (Apache Camel "
"Quarkus) master, but that's the only way forward.  We have the CI job "
"testing our QuickStart suite with Quarkus master and GraalVM master already."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2019-12-18-why-graalvm-19-2.adoc:67
msgid ""
"We also plan to add some RSS usage checks to this CI pipeline.  Funny story, "
"we had a different CI job that was testing RSS but its report failed with a "
"NPE.  ðŸ¤¦.  Murphy when you hit us."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2019-12-18-why-graalvm-19-2.adoc:69
msgid ""
"We hope you understand our cautious stance and the planned delay by a month "
"or so."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_posts/2019-12-18-why-graalvm-19-2.adoc:70
msgid ""
"In the meantime, a brand new Quarkus version is coming with a lot of "
"exciting stuff so be prepared!"
msgstr ""
